This is an early call for participation for MFPS XXVI (Mathematical=20
Foundations of Programming Semantics), to be held at the University of=20
Ottawa, May 6-10 2010 , partially sponsored by the US Office of Naval=20
Research and the Fields Institute.  Information on the aims and scope of =

the conference, as well as invited speakers, tutorials and special=20
sessions can be found at:

http://www.math.tulane.edu/~mfps/mfps26/MFPS_XXVI.html

The list of accepted papers will be available roughly mid-March.

The Fields registration webpage is at:=20
http://www.fields.utoronto.ca/programs/scientific/09-10/MFPS26/

Registration and early requests for student support can be done online =
at=20
the Fields Institute address above.

Note: some money is available to partially support graduate students,=20
postdocs and researchers without grants.  Those who wish to apply for =
this=20
support should do so right away on the Fields registration page (before=20
March 31). In your application for support, please state clearly what =
your=20
research program is, in what way MFPS is relevant to your research, and=20
whether you have access to other funds. Priority will be given to =
students=20
who do not have access to other funding for travel.

Graduate students please note: there will be a special student session =
of=20
short presentations, and students who wish to apply to speak should also =

tell us.

There is a planned conference banquet, to be announced soon.

Accommodation: we have reserved rooms in several hotels near campus, as=20
well as in the university residence. The university residence suites are =
a=20
very good deal:  a two room suite and kitchen is $90. On the local web=20
page of the event you will find more information on this. Please note =
that=20
in order to take advantage of the discount rate most bookings have to be =

done before April.  Here is the local web page:

http://aix1.uottawa.ca/~mwarren/MFPS/index.html

If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact one of the=20
organizers,

Richard Blute rblute@uottawa.ca
Philip Scott phil@site.uottawa.ca
Michael Warren mwarren@uottawa.ca


